60
0:02:53.26,000 --> 0:02:57,000
All holy history banned.

61
0:02:57.26,000 --> 0:03:01,000
Unwritten books predicted the future, projected the past.

62
0:03:01.26,000 --> 0:03:03,000
But my head unwraps

63
0:03:03.26,000 --> 0:03:06,000
around what appears limitless,

64
0:03:06.26,000 --> 0:03:09,000
man's creative violence.

65
0:03:09.26,000 --> 0:03:12,000
Whose son shall it be?

66
0:03:12.26,000 --> 0:03:16,000
Which male child will perish a new day?

67
0:03:16.26,000 --> 0:03:19,000
Our boys' deaths galvanize.

68
0:03:19.26,000 --> 0:03:21,000
We cherish corpses.

69
0:03:21.26,000 --> 0:03:23,000
We mourn women, complicated.

70
0:03:23.26,000 --> 0:03:25,000
Bitches get beat daily.

71
0:03:25.26,000 --> 0:03:28,000
Profits made, prophets ignored.

72
0:03:28.26,000 --> 0:03:31,000
War and tooth, enameled salted lemon childhoods.

73
0:03:31.26,000 --> 0:03:34,000
All colors run, none of us solid.

74
0:03:34.26,000 --> 0:03:37,000
Don't look for shadow behind me. I carry it within.

75
0:03:37.26,000 --> 0:03:4,000
I live cycles of light and darkness.

76
0:03:40.26,000 --> 0:03:42,000
Rhythm is half silence.

77
0:03:42.26,000 --> 0:03:45,000
I see now, I never was one and not the other.

78
0:03:45.26,000 --> 0:03:49,000
Sickness, health, tender violence.

79
0:03:49.26,000 --> 0:03:51,000
